During his address at the Thomas Nkobi cemetery for the 24th anniversary of Chris Hani's, President Jacob Zuma used the platform to speak out against racism.The president spoke about last week's countrywide anti-Zuma marches, where there were allegedly 'black people being called baboons' and some questionable placards.President Zuma further said that "the marches that took place last week demonstrated that racism is real."Zuma said the marches that took place last week proved that racism is still alive in SA. #ChrisHani @dailysunsa pic.twitter.com/96g8HhDnk9&mdash; Christopher Moagi (@ChrisMCMoagi) April 10, 2017